column11:
This lab is a resubmit because my first submission failed the auto-grader. My initial submitted code did not return the right item for the item at index 1. Instead of printing the Id and inventory number, it would print out the "Item is not in stock" line.

Mr. Ferrante and I debugged this problem together by using a whiteboard and marker, and essentially took a smaller chunk of the txt file to sample a small list of items. While continuing to debug my code at home, I realized that the first and middle indexes become the same at one point if I were to enter the ID value for index 1. And since these two indexes = 0, instead of first being changed to mid + 1, it went to the first if statement, mid = (first + mid) / 2. Since this is true because mid and first were 0 at the time, it returned -1. To fix this, I added an if statement before the if statement I just talked about, and whenever mid equals first, i increment the middle index value by 1. This way, my program will continue functioning until the middle index equals the index of the item I am looking for.
